**IN ANOTHER PLACE, IN ANOTHER TIME, PALAVER IS HELD:**

Inside a PRIVATE JET, two INTERLOCUTORS face each other across a table.

ONE: The Realm seems to be... a backdoor into the mind. A way to smooth over some of the demands of a conscious mind. A way to fufill Maslow's hierarchy without _actually_ doing so, if you will.
TWO: But happiness is happiness. Why should we worry about the mechanism? You place value on Maslow, but Maslow is arbitrary. The mechanisms of evolution are arbitrary. The two strongest correlates to happiness are relationship status and job satisfaction. Utterly meaningless when considered objectively.[f1]
ONE: But if we are to abandon evolution, abandon our only guide through the darkness (if you will), then don't we in some way sacrifice our humanity, in the deepest sense?
TWO: We aren't abandoning our humanity. We're creating a new humanity.
ONE: But the humanity that we have created is deeply unsatisfying.
TWO: Who are you to judge? Who are you to say that 20 billion humans are wrong? Are somehow _in_human? How can you possibly say that your opinion is worth more than theirs? 
_A pause fills the conversation._ 
TWO: There is one advantage, though.
ONE: What's that?
TWO: The Game provides a nice solution to the Fermi problem.[9]

